On the {}_LE_r pages of the spectral sequence defined by (\mathrm {s} K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}},L), the recurrent filtration and the two direct filtrations defined by \operatorname {Dec}_1(W) agree; similarly, on the {}_LE_r(\mathrm {s} K_\mathbb {C}), the recurrent filtration and the two direct filtrations induced by F agree. We denoted these filtrations again by W and F (respectively).
For r\geqslant 1, ({}_LE_r,W,F) is a mixed Hodge A-structure (). The differentials d_r are morphisms of mixed Hodge A-structures.
The filtration L on \operatorname {H}^\bullet (\mathrm {s} K) is a filtration in the category of mixed Hodge structures, and
